</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="70" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,386,1419]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,818,843]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This unique species can be separated from its congeners by the presence of a small tubercle in the middle of the frontal suture (
<figureCitation box="[657,742,854,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–57" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1716,1739]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,295,1694]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[171,1412,295,1697]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 52–57. Lateral side of pronotum (52, 53, 57), lateral elytra intervals (54, 55) and head in dorsal view (56) of Macroderes species. 52, M. politulus Preudhomme de Borre, 1880; 53, M. minutus Frolov &amp; Scholtz, 2005; 54, M. fornicatus Sharp, 1880; 55, 57, M. bias (Olivier, 1789); 56, M. undulatus Preudhomme de Borre, 1880." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606186/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
), elytra having smooth, elevated areas in the middle of each interstria with sparse punctuation (
<figureCitation box="[539,620,890,915]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–69" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,474,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[158,1427,474,1901]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 64–69. Punctuation of the base of pronotum (64, 65) and sculpture of second elytra intervals (66–69) of Macroderes species. 64, M. amplior Frolov &amp; Scholtz, 2005; 65, 67, M. fornicatus Sharp, 1880; 66, M. bias (Olivier, 1789); 68, M. undulatus Preudhomme de Borre, 1880; 69, M. nitidus Harold, 1877." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606190/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
) and metasternum lacking any punctuation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="70" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,386,1419]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,507,926,951]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Habitat and distribution.</emphasis>
The species was collected from uncertain localities in the southern part of the 
<collectingRegion box="[151,412,962,987]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Western Cape Province</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[427,494,962,987]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Macroderes species." pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), however, in general the southern part of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1005,1160,963,987]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Western Cape</collectingRegion>
as described by Olsen 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">et al.</emphasis>
(2001) is a moist coastal hilly area delimited by the lowland Fynbos biome and Renosterveld eco-region in the north and the coast of Renosterveld in the east.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,386,1419]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1070,1095]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H." box="[477,756,1070,1095]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" pagination="373 - 393" refId="ref21694" refString="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H. (2005) Revision of the southern African genus Macroderes Westwood (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 40 (3 - 4), 373 - 393. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2004.10697429" type="journal article" year="2005">Frolov &amp; Scholtz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[809,868,1071,1095]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preudhomme de Borre" authorityYear="1880" box="[906,1062,1070,1094]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westwoodi">
<emphasis box="[906,1062,1070,1094]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. westwoodi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preudhomme de Borre" authorityYear="1880" box="[1117,1265,1070,1094]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulatus">
<emphasis box="[1117,1265,1070,1094]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. undulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are curated for in the same collection (J. Thompson’s collection) and they might even have been collected from the same uncertain locality. The observations of 
<bibRefCitation author="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H." box="[490,776,1142,1167]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" pagination="373 - 393" refId="ref21694" refString="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H. (2005) Revision of the southern African genus Macroderes Westwood (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 40 (3 - 4), 373 - 393. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2004.10697429" type="journal article" year="2005">Frolov &amp; Scholtz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
on these two species emphasise their similarity in many morphological aspects; they are similar in general body shape, the presence of a tubercle on the frontal suture, the same pronotal punctures and weakly distinct punctures on the metasternum, although they are different in elytral sculpture. As we have not seen the 
<typeStatus box="[569,628,1251,1275]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preudhomme de Borre" authorityYear="1880" box="[672,831,1251,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westwoodi">
<emphasis box="[672,831,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. westwoodi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preudhomme de Borre" authorityYear="1880" box="[892,1043,1251,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulatus">
<emphasis box="[892,1043,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. undulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H." pageId="29" pageNumber="70" pagination="373 - 393" refId="ref21694" refString="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H. (2005) Revision of the southern African genus Macroderes Westwood (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 40 (3 - 4), 373 - 393. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2004.10697429" type="journal article" year="2005">Frolov &amp; Scholtz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
in synonymising 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preudhomme de Borre" authorityYear="1880" box="[429,585,1286,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westwoodi">
<emphasis box="[429,585,1286,1310]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. westwoodi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Preudhomme de Borre" authorityYear="1880" box="[651,800,1286,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulatus">
<emphasis box="[651,800,1286,1310]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. undulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as their reasoning stated above, regarding the subject is sound.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,386,1419]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">The species has been listed as threatened in the IUCN red list under the B1ab criterion due to it is limited and vulnerable range (Davis 2013).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
